[I] Renders realistic skies in real time with openGL

[T] With Stellarium, you really see what you can see with
[T] your eyes, binoculars or a small telescope. It displays
[T] stars, constellations, planets, nebulas and others things
[T] like ground, landscape, atmophere, etc ...

